The paper deals with differential privacy, which is a topic in cryptography and security (cs.CR). It also involves counting problems and sample complexity, which are topics in data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of multiple messages per user is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests it may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.DM) where similar techniques are used to improve accuracy.
